1. Batch Consumer

factory.setBatchListener(true)

Receive multiple records together.

Example
List<ConsumerRecord<...>>

instead of one message.

Benefits: higher throughput, fewer polls, better performance

2. Manual Offset Commit

enable-auto-commit: false

and:

acknowledgment.acknowledge();

Commit offsets ONLY after successful processing.

Benefits : no message loss, precise control, reliable processing

3. Retry Mechanism

new FixedBackOff(2000L, 3)

Automatically retry temporary failures.

Benefits : temporary recovery, avoids unnecessary failures, improves resilience

4. Dead Letter Topic (DLT)

orders.DLT

Store permanently failed messages.

Benefits: prevents infinite retry loops, isolates bad messages, supports manual investigation

5. DLT Consumer

@KafkaListener(topics = "orders.DLT")

Process failed messages separately.

Real Uses: alerting, auditing, DB storage, reprocessing

6. Without Concurrency

You would create:

Consumer-1 → Partition 0
Consumer-2 → Partition 1
Consumer-3 → Partition 2

Meaning:

3 separate consumer instances
more code/configuration
more deployment complexity

With Concurrency
===============

You create:

factory.setConcurrency(3);

inside ONE application.

Spring internally creates:

3 consumer threads

automatically.

